				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I thought dB was logarithmic, which I always thought meant 2dB = 2x louder than 1dB, 3dB = 2x louder than 2dB, etc...</div>You're thinking of base-2 logarithmic. In brief,<br /><br /><ul><li>Bels are base-10 logarithmic. 1 bel is 10 times the power of 0 bels.</li><li>1 bel is 10 decibels.</li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decibel" class="postlink">Wikipedia says</a> &quot;in most applications power is proportional to the square of amplitude.&quot;</li></ul><br />Putting that all together, 6 decibels is close to 2 times the amplitude of 0 decibels.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

